In Nigeria the conflict is reaching a crisis point, skirmishes over land have escalated into something much bigger - ethnic and religious violence. 

Clashes between farmers who are mostly Christian and herdsmen who are Muslim are making headlines around the country, thousands of people have been killed. The town of Barkin Ladi (BAR-kin LAA-di) in central Nigeria used to be a crisis hotspot. But about two years ago it stopped. 

The BBC's Stephanie Hegarty travelled to the community of Barkin Ladi and found one of the reasons for that peace, could be hidden underground...

